AstraCore Neo — Dual Licence (DRAFT, subject to formal review)
=================================================================

Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Astracore AI Technologies Private Limited.

The AstraCore Neo repository contains two bodies of work with two different
licences. A single file's licence is determined by its top-level directory.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Apache License 2.0  — Python SDK, compiler, tools, scripts, documentation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scope (Apache-2.0 licensed):

    src/           Python platform SDK (hal, memory, compute, safety,
                   security, telemetry, dms, connectivity, models)
    tools/         Compiler, quantiser, reference runtime, frontends,
                   build scripts, Verilator runners
    tests/         Test suites (both for tools/ and rtl/ cocotb glue)
    docs/          Architecture documents, spec-sheet provenance,
                   audit findings, markdown guides
    scripts/       Data-prep, export, and utility scripts
    PLAN.md        Project plan
    README.md      Repository README

These files are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 ("the
License"); you may not use these files except in compliance with the
License. You may obtain a copy of the License at:

    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
limitations under the License.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Source-Available Evaluation Licence — Hardware RTL and silicon artefacts
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scope (Evaluation-licence only — NOT open source):

    rtl/              SystemVerilog RTL (all modules)
    sim/              cocotb testbenches that exercise rtl/
    constraints/      FPGA timing / IO constraints
    fpga/             FPGA bring-up packages (AWS F1, Arty A7, etc.)
    asic/             OpenLane / synthesis configuration and run outputs
    data/models/      Reference model artefacts
    data/calibration/ Pre-processed calibration/evaluation tensors

Permitted uses (no separate agreement needed):

    a. Non-commercial evaluation — reading, building, simulating, modifying
       locally for the purpose of technical evaluation of AstraCore Neo
       IP and publishing evaluation results.
    b. Academic research and classroom use, with attribution.
    c. Reproducing this repository for audit, due-diligence, or
       standards-certification review.

Prohibited uses (without a separate written licence from Astracore AI
Technologies Private Limited):

    a. Fabricating or selling silicon derived from these files.
    b. Sub-licensing, redistributing, or publishing modified copies of
       these files as a competing open-source project.
    c. Incorporating these files into a commercial product.
    d. Filing patents on derived inventions.

Commercial licensing: contact <licensing@astracore.example> (placeholder —
formal contact address to be confirmed).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Notices
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* This file is a DRAFT intended to establish a license posture in the
  repository. Both licence texts should be reviewed by counsel before
  external publication. The prohibited-uses list above is intentionally
  conservative and may be broadened in a final version.

* Third-party packages vendored under `.venv/` and `.venv-export/` carry
  their own licences (see the per-package LICENSE files therein).

* The "Partially Open-Source SDK" phrase used in the AstraCore Neo spec
  sheet refers specifically to the Apache-2.0 licensed Python tools and
  documentation above, not to the RTL.
